    full: `When this earth itself was torn into pieces, was it right?
In this world, everyone longs for their freedom.

Is it wrong to think so?
Then why was the land of this earth divided,
Though, in truth, we have no rightful claim upon it—
Is it wrong, then, to desire a piece of it?

They say that after death, only our deeds follow us,
So is our presence in this world not essential to anyone?

When we have divided this very earth, then what is the heart for?
The heart that knows no borders, that understands no distance,
That never sees one human as separate from another—
Is that heart now also guilty?

This soil belongs to all, it resides in everyone,
Yet we have sliced it with religion, caste, and borders.
Perhaps that is why, even today, man is alone—
Trapped between the boundaries he himself has drawn,
Fighting shadows of his own making.`,
