    id: 50,
    title: "When my faith begins to flicker like a tired falling flame,",
    excerpt:
      "You hold my trembling hands and softly whisper my name. / You breathe life into the dreams I once buried deep inside, / You turn my scattered hopes into something I wear with pride.",
    full: `You hold my trembling hands and softly whisper my name.
You breathe life into the dreams I once buried deep inside,
You turn my scattered hopes into something I wear with pride.

You say, “Don’t count your scars, they are just stars you’ve earned.”
You show me how every closed door was a lesson learned.
You paint courage on my heart when it feels torn and gray,
And teach me that the sun still rises on the darkest day.

You never feared the crooked paths or the twists of fate,
You walked beside me, slow and calm, never in haste or hate.
You didn’t follow the roads drawn on maps or on sand,
You danced with the waves like the sea is your homeland.

You told me love isn’t always loud—sometimes it’s quiet and warm,
Sometimes it’s the shelter that keeps you safe in the storm.
It’s the voice that reminds you, when the world gets too loud,
That even a broken soul can still wear a shining shroud.

I looked for perfection once, but now I clearly see—
Love was not flawless, love was simply you and me.
A boy who held my fears so gently in his hand,
Who believed in me more than I could ever understand.

You are the poetry I never meant to write,
A melody of hope in my silent night.
You’re not just love, not just someone passing by—
You’re the boy who knows my heart better than I.`,
