    id: 53,
    title: "The Accused Heart",
    excerpt:
      "Blamed for loving, punished for feeling. / Is it a crime to love, / or is it not a crime?",
    full: `Blamed for loving, punished for feeling.

Is it a crime to love,
or is it not a crime?

Is loving you a sin,
or is the world simply thirsty
for another soul to burn?

If love is forbidden,
why did the gods carve their fate
into each other’s arms?
And if it is pure,
why was my heart dragged
into a courtroom of eyes?

Why was my love strangled
before it could even breathe?
Why did I stand alone
while a thousand whispers
stabbed me like quiet knives?

Why did I drown
in the dark flood of rumours—
waves made by people
who know nothing of storms?

Why did you leave me
to face those midnight trials,
those questions that clawed
at the walls of my chest?

If my crime is love,
then let the world hang me
for loving too deeply.

But if it is not,
then free me from these shadows,
untie me from the ropes
of judgments I never deserved.

Tell me…
before I break again,
before the darkness closes in—

Is my love my crime,
or is this cruel world
the real murderer?`,
