    id: 158,
    title: "“A Man Still Breathing, Yet Gone”",
    excerpt:
      "Today, I witnessed something strange— / something my eyes had never known before. / In those eyes, I saw a man…",
    full: `Today, I witnessed something strange—
something my eyes had never known before.
In those eyes, I saw a man…
not living, but breaking—
silently crying, drowning in his own agony,
begging love to stay a little longer.

Without her,
life felt like a burden he could no longer carry.
His heart wasn’t shattered—
no, it was worse…
it felt like it had stopped beating,
while his body still pretended to live.

There was a pain so deep within him
that even words felt ashamed to exist.
He hid it—
behind quiet smiles,
behind distant glances—
never letting anyone see the storm inside.

And now,
he pushes the world away,
not because he hates it—
but because he fears being seen.

All he ever wanted now…
was not questions,
not sympathy—

just someone—
who could understand his silence,
without him ever having to speak.`,
