    title: "The Secret of the Incomplete Night",
    excerpt:
      "What can we tell / to those shadowed nights, broken as they lay, / where every silhouette whispered its own tale,",
    full: `What can we tell
to those shadowed nights, broken as they lay,
where every silhouette whispered its own tale,
and even silence trembled in fear?

The moon revealed only half its face,
as if someone had stolen its courage.
The wind asked names in hushed whispers,
and only unnamed echoes answered.

Shadows shifted on the walls,
sometimes in windows, sometimes along alleyways,
yet the secret remained—
a night that may never be complete.

Counting hours, we watched
how many dreams shatter,
and how many longings
scatter silently into the dark.

The stillness stretched its hand,
drawing us inward,
where every step
was surrounded by old memories
and unspoken questions.

Then a voice came—softly, almost unseen,
“Are you ready to know?”
We nodded,
yet deep inside we knew,
some secrets are meant only for the night.

Morning came…
but the mystery of that night
still clings to our eyelids,
like sleep refusing to release.
And whenever darkness returns,
we search for it again—
a night
that may never be complete.`,
