    id: 265,
    title: "PART 4 OF 5 POTERY",
    excerpt: `"What Stayed" / Healing did not arrive as relief. / It arrived as balance.`,
    full: `"What Stayed"

Healing did not arrive as relief.
It arrived as balance.

The ground beneath me stopped shifting.
Not because it forgot the weight,
but because it learned
how to carry it without collapse.

I noticed first in my breathing—
how it no longer argued with my chest,
how silence stopped feeling like punishment
and began to feel like space.

The land was unchanged,
yet everything responded differently.
Wind moved through me
without searching for exits.
Light rested where it fell,
unafraid of being temporary.

I no longer measured myself
by what was lost.
Loss had already done its work—
shaped the terrain,
deepened the roots,
made room for things
that do not need explanation.

Some memories softened.
Others remained sharp,
but they no longer demanded attention.
Like stones in a riverbed,
they stayed where they were placed,
no longer cutting the current.

I found myself capable of pause.
Not retreat,
not escape—
just pause.
The rare ability
to stop without fear
that everything would disappear.

Even love felt different now.
Quieter.
Unattached to outcome.
No longer a wound looking for meaning,
but a presence that knew
how to stay without consuming.

I stopped waiting for myself to return
to who I was before.
That person had already become soil.
From them, something steadier grew—
less hopeful, perhaps,
but more real.

The nights grew gentler.
Darkness stopped pressing questions into me.
It simply arrived,
did what it was meant to do,
and left.

In the morning,
I stood where I always had,
but my feet felt placed,
not stranded.

Healing, I learned,
is not the absence of pain.
It is the end of resistance.
The moment the earth stops fighting
the rain that shaped it.

So this is what stayed—
not joy,
not certainty,
but a quiet agreement
between me and the world
to let things be as they are
and still remain.

And somehow,
that was enough.`,
