    id: 266,
    title: "PART 5 OF 5 POTERY",
    excerpt: `"And Still, I Remain " / I did not return to the world unchanged. / The world did not ask me to.`,
    full: `"And Still, I Remain "

I did not return to the world unchanged.
The world did not ask me to.

We met again
the way old companions do—
without explanations,
without apologies,
aware of what had passed
and choosing not to reopen it.

The land held my history quietly.
Every step knew where I had been.
Nothing needed proving anymore.

I no longer searched the sky
for signs meant only for me.
The sky was never withholding—
I simply hadn’t known
how to stand beneath it without asking.

What once felt like absence
now felt like margin—
space enough to move,
to breathe,
to exist without narration.

Attachment loosened its grip.
Not because it failed,
but because it had finished teaching me
how deeply I was capable of holding.

Love did not leave.
It changed temperature.
It became something I could carry
without burning.

The past stayed where it belonged—
not behind me,
not ahead of me,
but within the soil that supports my weight.

I stopped trying to be understood.
The earth never needed explanation
to keep me.

If healing has a sound,
it is this—
the quiet agreement
between what I was
and what I am now
to stop pulling apart.

So I remain.
Not searching.
Not closing.
Not opening excessively.

Just here.

Like land after seasons of learning
how to survive weather,
how to accept light,
how to hold life
without asking it to stay.

And that is how the cycle ends—
not with certainty,
but with presence.`,
