    id: 279,
    title: "Escaping is easy.",
    excerpt: "It asks for nothing— / no patience, / no endurance,",
    full: `It asks for nothing—
no patience,
no endurance,
no quiet listening to the ache
that settles in the chest at night.

Leaving feels lighter.
Like closing a door
before the room can ask
why you stayed so long.

But staying—
staying is heavier.

Staying means waking up
with the same wounds
and choosing not to run from them.
It means letting life touch you
even when it hurts
in places you don’t have names for.

To be part of life
is to accept its weight—
the slow days,
the unanswered questions,
the silence that doesn’t heal
but still asks you to remain.

There is no applause in this.
No one calls it bravery.
It is just a quiet decision
made every day
to not disappear.

And maybe that is enough.
Not happiness.
Not peace.

Just the courage
to stay
and exist
where escape would have been easier.`,
